title.narrative: Enhanced evidence and guidance on supply chain strengthening and optimization

description.narrative: The procurement load in 2021 multiplied considerably due to the COVID-19 response, with local procurement volumes increasing from US$77 million in 2019 to US$111.8 million in 2021. ESARO provided hands-on support to COVAX ESAR governments for procurement of vaccines. This included guiding COs and facilitating multiple vaccine shipments and providing real-time technical support, which prevented vaccine losses due to stocks expiring. Acknowledging the delicate dynamics related to COVID-19 supplies, ESARO played a strategic role in negotiating with major African stakeholders and the wider supply community, especially by promoting local manufacturing capabilities | Status:On-track | As-of Date:23/03/2022
